Hablo espanol pero no escribo muy bien.  Vivo en un pueblo chiquito en
Tennessee.  Me gusta leer las mensajes en espanol.

I read recently that some critics see Mirror as a continuation of Ivan's
Childhood.  I've only seen Ivan's Childhood once and don't remember it
well, but I can see how that connection could be made.  However, this
connection has never been discussed to my knowledge on this list. Anybody
care to have a go?  I'm curious.  Are Russians just as nostalgic for WWII
as we North Americans are?  For us (esp. in cinema) WWII has come to
represent a time when the world was black and white and clear
distinctions could be made between right and wrong.  I'm wondering if
Tark's war movies (Mirror, Ivan) have any of that going on in them. 
Thomas

